    "In SR, achieving a recall of ≥ 95% is crucial to minimise the omission of relevant articles (i.e., reducing false negatives, FN) (O' Mara-Eves et al. 2015).",
    "However, a precision-recall trade-off exists where increasing recall decreases precision and vice versa.",
    "Consequently, some studies have employed techniques to enhance precision while maintaining high recall rates.",
    "These techniques include feature enrichment, resampling methods, and query expansion.",
    "Table 2 summarises the methods proposed in relevant studies to maintain recall rates and improve precision."
  ],
